[[File:St Nicholas - Cornish - Gage 03.jpg|thumb|The facility shared by the Bright Water Waldorf School and [[Gage Academy of Art]], pictured here in 2009.]] '''Bright Water Waldorf School''' is a Preschool through Grade Eight [[Waldorf School]] in [[Seattle]], Washington, located in the historic St. Nicholas Building on Capitol Hill;<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.sos.wa.gov/charities/search-app.aspx#/detail-charity/6346|title=Bright Water Waldorf Society, Charity Profile Report #6346|last=|first=|date=|work=|access-date=2017-08-01|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|publisher=Charities - WA Secretary of State|quote=Registration Status: Failure to Register/Renew}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://community.seattletimes.nwsource.com/schoolguide/profile.php?results=search&building_id=1422&search=criteria&grade_low=K&grade_high=12&school_zip=ZIP%20code&pl_code%5B%5D=P|title=Seattle Times {{!}} School Guide {{!}} Bright Water School|last=|first=|date=|work=The Seattle Times|access-date=2017-08-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110519090030/http://community.seattletimes.nwsource.com/schoolguide/profile.php?results=search&building_id=1422&search=criteria&grade_low=K&grade_high=12&school_zip=ZIP%20code&pl_code%5B%5D=P|archive-date=2011-05-19|dead-url=Yes}}</ref> the building is a designated Seattle Landmark.<ref>[http://www.seattle.gov/Documents/Departments/Neighborhoods/HistoricPreservation/Landmarks/RelatedDocuments/st-nicholas-lakeside-school-designation-nomination.pdf Report on Designation: St. Nicholas School], The City of Seattle Landmarks Preservation Board, 1981-07-29. Accessed 2015-07-30.</ref> Its grade school program includes Japanese, Spanish, Handwork, Woodworking, Eurhythmy, Orchestra, and Band.
Bright Water Waldorf School was founded in 1998 and is a Candidate Member of the [[Northwest Association of Independent Schools]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nwais.org/page.cfm?p=51|title=NWAIS: Bright Water Waldorf School|website=www.nwais.org|access-date=2017-08-01}}</ref> and a Developing School in the Association of Waldorf Schools of North America (AWSNA).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://waldorfeducation.org/relid/622351/src/trakkware/accountid/296/isvars/default/find_a_school.htm|title=Association of Waldorf Schools of North America -> Find a School -> Bright Water Waldorf School|last=|first=|date=|website=waldorfeducation.org|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2017-08-01}}</ref>
