'''Education in [[Dominica]]''' is compulsory from ages 5 to 16.<ref name=ilab>[http://www.dol.gov/ilab/media/reports/iclp/tda2001/dominica.htm "Dominica"]. ''2001 Findings on the Worst Forms of Child Labor''. [[Bureau of International Labor Affairs]], [[U.S. Department of Labor]] (2002). ''This article incorporates text from this source, which is in the [[public domain]].</ref>  The gross primary enrollment rate was 100.4{{clarify|date=February 2016}} percent in 1991 and 98.2 percent in 1998, and the net primary enrollment rate was 88.7 percent in 1991 and 88.8 percent in 1998.<ref name=ilab/> Primary school attendance rates were unavailable for Dominica as of 2001. Poor physical conditions in many primary schools affect the quality of education, while some schools are overcrowded, limiting access to primary education, particularly for children living in urban areas around the capital. Poverty and work on family banana farms during the harvest season can affect school attendance, but other employment does not pull minors out of school. There is a significant Carib Indian population in Dominica and schools on the [[Carib Territory]] are reported to have fewer resources.<ref name=ilab/>

[[List of universities in Dominica|Tertiary-level educations institutions]] include [[Dominica State College]]<ref>[http://dsc.dm/ "Dominica State College"].</ref><ref name=nab>[http://nab.gov.dm/services/accreditation/accredited-institutions "Accredited Institutions"]. National Accreditation Board of Dominica (2016).</ref>
, the [[University of the West Indies|University of the West Indies Open Campus]],<ref>[https://www.open.uwi.edu/dominica/ "Open Campus Dominica"]. University of the West Indies (2016).</ref> [[All Saints University School of Medicine]],<ref>http://www.allsaintsuniversity.org/</ref> [[International University for Graduate Studies]],<ref name=nab/><ref>[https://iugrad.edu.dm/about-iugs/contact-us.html "Contact Us"]. IUGS (2016).</ref> [[New World University]],<ref name=nwu>[http://newworld.ac/about/history "Our History"]. New World University (2016).</ref> and [[Ross University School of Medicine]].<ref>http://www.rossu.edu/medical-school/</ref>

